The article discusses the nomination of Robert Wilkie as the Secretary of the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) and highlights his qualifications and commitment to serving military families and veterans. President Donald J. Trump expresses confidence in Wilkie's ability to do an incredible job at the VA. Wilkie has previously served as Acting Secretary of the VA and Under Secretary of Defense for Personnel & Readiness, where he fought for military families and veterans. His nomination has received praise from the veterans community.